<br>
It is a caster pet, it shouldn't even try to melee, give it the same ability like the castermobs in Forest in PoS have, they root themself if they get agro.<br>
This ability would have some uses.<br>
<br>
It is still a firepet, give it back its old skills. Firelemental attack (or rather give it an upgraded version that do ~180 dmg), this way it would have a steady dps since it goes off every 6 sec, fireelemantal attack 1 is slightly to low dps, but a ~180pt DD would add a steady 30dps, still just half off any other of our pets.<br>
Also give it back its Fireelemental aura ... well .. its a firepet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 614<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 6:23:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fire pet</span><hr size=1> They don't root themselves do they? They just chain cast, thus never move. If they were rooting themselves, they'd have to chain cast it, since my 2k nuke would break it every time. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 615<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 6:25:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fire pet</span><hr size=1> Oh and also...<br>
<br>
I'd rather have a shadowknight pet. Unless it had high hps, that'd make improved reclaim a worthwhile skill again. <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hobiewankenobe>Hobiewankenobe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 433<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 7:53:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myweb.thump.net/1363/pictures/Gonn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fire pet</span><hr size=1> Fire pets suck, simply put. NO excuses for it to be acsting the same spells it does at level 52. At least before 65 it had situational uses for stunning mobs, but as of now, it's useless. Pure and utter crap and waste of a spectral IMHO. I don't know anyway to make it useful really...i'd rather have a pet meleeing then casting lvl 20 nukes, but if it casts higher level nukes, wizards will start complaining. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.power3d.com/Arch/member_inv.asp?member_id=263">Hobie Wan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
65th level slacker mage<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.power3d.com/Arch/">Arch of Chaos (Terris-Thule)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#333333>(1/1/03 1:53:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fire pet</span><hr size=1> I was having fun with the Voc:Fire pet one day in East Commons.  I thought it was fun seeing it nuke orcs and lions and bugs.  Then a griffon jumped me.  I went to run through my pet to get aggro of me, and Jabober was half a zone away casting O'Keils Embers on himself.  Nice pet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#333333>(1/1/03 1:17:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mobs..</span><hr size=1> Forest mobs in PoS, the druid versions root themself if they agro, agro them and them and they just stand there try nuke you, if you move outside their casting range they still just sit there looking at you and ofcourse agro ever single mobs that pass close to them.<br>
They will stand there until they lose agro (like memblur).<br>
<br>
This skill would be usefull for a mage since having a pet that would just stay fixed and root and nuke (they will root if mobs try and run. It would been an exelent agrokite pet, with luck it also would snare (it do that too from time to time). I would love a rooted firepet, it would make it usefull in some places.<br>
<br>
Combine the rooted skill with its Fireelemental attack and you will have a steady dps from it (even if the dps would only be 10dps with Fireelemantal attack 1).<br>
<br>
Ofcourse upgrade its spell to match PoP would be the best solution. It need to be smarter .. Cast a 50pt DD with stun on a mob that can't be stunned (with that spell) is totaly useless, if it on the other hand would switch to pure nukes on those mobs it atleast would do some dmg, if it also would try and avoid dmg like a normal wizard would it would be even nicer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fabbz>Fabbz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#333333>(1/1/03 2:42:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mobs..</span><hr size=1> the level 20 wizzy nue would be fine if they just changed the AI.<br>
<br>
have it randomly pick between 2 AI's, &quot;stun&quot; and &quot;nuke&quot;<br>
<br>
each AI casts one spell only.  the mana shock for nuke, i think that's it's best one.  and the stun for stun (duh)<br>
